description.text:
Our Backend team mainly focuses on features, integrations, scalability and security for our platform to support our next-gen, AAA, 3rd Person Co-Op Shooter game. We are taking our game development to the next level and we are looking for an experienced developer to join the team!

Your contribution
As a Backend Developer / DevOps Engineer your main tasks and responsibilities are:

- Implement online features for our next flagship, AAA game;
- Set up and configure third party applications and databases to facilitate a high volume multiplayer project;
- Develop and maintain both stateful and stateless web applications, currently written in C# (.NET core);
- Support our devs with the integration of new backend features;
- Create web applications backed by databases such as MS-SQL, or similar.


Our requirements
We’re looking for a Backend Developer / DevOps Engineer to join our kickass team! :

- Experience in the video game development or -publishing industry, in particular as a developer working on the server-stack of multiplayer games;
- Experience with Backend / API Development in C# or Java;
- Experience with database technology and maintenance of technologies such as SQL, Key-Value databases, Message Queuing, etc;
- Experience with micro services architecture;



Bonus qualifications
- Going full stack you will need C++ skills for integrating online features directly in the game;
- Experience with HTML, Javascript/TypeScript and CSS.


Our project
We are working on a 3rd person shooter featuring next-gen graphics, innovative co-op and agency for the community to alter the course of the game. This AAA game will share the satirical humor that fans of our previous games know and love.

Practical information
Scope: Full-time, 40 hours per week. We offer a permanent position and relocation aid for the right candidate.

Location: Stockholm

If you think that this position matches your background and skills, we would love to hear from you. We ask that your application always include relevant work samples or a link to your portfolio.
